One Pot Pumpkin Pasta with Parmesan and Kale

2 tbsp evoo
1 small yellow onion
2 cloves garlic, finely chopped
3/4 tsp crushed red pepper
8 oz spaghetti or linguini
4 c low sodium chicken or vegetable stock
15 oz can pure pumpkin puree
1 bunch kale, stems removed and leaves roughly chopped
freshly shaved parmesan cheese for serving

In a large, straight sided skillet or dutch oven, heat the oil over medium high heat. Add the onion and saute until soft and translucent, 3-4 min. Add the garlic and crushed red pepper and saute 1 min. Add the pasta, stock, and pumpkin puree, season to taste with salt and pepper, and stir to combine. Raise the heat to high and bring to a boil. Continue boiling, stirring every 30 s or so and adjusting the heat as needed for 7 min. Add the kale, reduce the heat to medium high, and simmer, stirring frequently until the pasta is al dente and the sauce is thick, 3-5 min. Season to taste with salt, pepper, and crushed red pepper. Serve with parmesan on top.
